msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/date"
msgid "June 17th, 1942 · Sevastopol, Crimea"
msgstr "17 de junio de 1942 - Sebastopol, Crimea"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/mission_option_select1"
msgid "Select your Doctrine for the mission:"
msgstr "Seleccione su Doctrina para la misión:"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/doctrine_all_round"
msgid "Doctrine: All-Round, 213th Infantry Regiment"
msgstr "Doctrina: Equilibrada, Regimiento de Infantería 213"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/doctrine_challenge"
msgid "Doctrine: Challenge! Sturmpioniere or death!"
msgstr "Doctrina: ¡Desafío! ¡Sturmpioniere o muerte!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/doctrine_offensive"
msgid "Doctrine: Offensive, 173rd Engineer Battalion"
msgstr "Doctrina: Ofensiva, 173º Batallón de Ingenieros"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/lose"
msgid "You lost all your troops!"
msgstr "¡Has perdido todas tus tropas!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/name"
msgid "The Siege of Sevastopol <c(a655af)>[DLC]</c>"
msgstr "El sitio de Sebastopol <c(a655af)>[DLC]</c>"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/name_big"
msgid "The Siege of Sevastopol"
msgstr "El sitio de Sebastopol"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/01"
msgid ""
"Soldaten! Listen up!! We have succeeded in crossing the Belbek river and "
"establishing a small bridgehead. But the hardest part is still to come..."
msgstr ""
"¡Soldados! ¡Escuchad! Hemos logrado cruzar el río Belbek y establecer una "
"pequeña cabeza de puente. Pero la parte más difícil aún está por venir..."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/02"
msgid ""
"We need to break into the main valley positions and clear a way through the "
"minefield for our main force of attack. Only then can we attack haccius "
"ridge, which is our main objective today. "
msgstr ""
"Tenemos que irrumpir en las posiciones principales del valle y despejar un "
"camino a través del campo de minas para nuestra fuerza principal de ataque. "
"Sólo entonces podremos atacar la colina de Haccius, que es nuestro objetivo "
"principal hoy."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/03"
msgid ""
"We need to start by advancing eastward and clearing several strongpoints. "
"Los geht's!!"
msgstr ""
"Tenemos que empezar avanzando hacia el este y despejando varios puntos "
"fuertes. ¡¡Los geht's!!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/04"
msgid ""
"We now control the Belbek valley and can start our attack on coastal battery "
"30."
msgstr ""
"Ahora controlamos el valle de Belbek y podemos empezar nuestro ataque a la "
"batería costera 30."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/05"
msgid ""
"We are all set for the attack. We can start off with a frontal attack to "
"take the main battery, or we can try to attack one or more flanks to begin "
"with. It is your choice, Herr Leutnant."
msgstr ""
"Ya tenemos todo listo para el ataque. Podemos empezar con un ataque frontal "
"para tomar la batería principal, o podemos intentar atacar uno o más flancos "
"como primer paso. Es tu elección, Herr Leutnant."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/06"
msgid ""
"Look out for secondary minefields and AT positions. They may prove dangerous "
"for our advance, be on the loukout for any soviet counter attack as well, "
"the enemy is not going to give up the ridge without a fight..."
msgstr ""
"Estate atento a los campos de minas secundarios y a las posiciones "
"antitanque. Pueden ser peligrosas para nuestro avance, estad atentos a "
"cualquier contraataque soviético también, el enemigo no va a renunciar a la "
"colina sin luchar..."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/07"
msgid ""
"I am placing under your command our Thor siege mortar. Show those soviets "
"what it means to be under the yoke of the Wehrmacht's heaviest artillery! It "
"will require a whole detachment of resupply vehicles to keep it in operation!"
msgstr ""
"Pongo bajo tu mando nuestro mortero de asedio Thor. Demuestra a esos "
"soviéticos lo que significa estar bajo el yugo de la artillería más pesada "
"de la Wehrmacht ¡Se necesitará todo un destacamento de vehículos de "
"abastecimiento para mantenerlo en funcionamiento!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/08"
msgid ""
"With the additional reinforcements, I expect you to breack through the "
"soviet defences and reach the battery. High command will expect no further "
"delays. Annihilate the enemy!"
msgstr ""
"Con los refuerzos adicionales, espero que consigas romper las defensas "
"soviéticas y llegues a la batería. El alto mando no tolerará más retrasos. "
"¡Aniquila al enemigo!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/09"
msgid ""
"The enemy has also deployed marines from the Black Sea Fleet to reinforce "
"their lines. Beware! These are tough nuts to crack, you will need to throw "
"everything you have at them!"
msgstr ""
"El enemigo también ha desplegado marines de la Flota del Mar Negro para "
"reforzar sus líneas. Cuidado, Esta gente siempre nos da los peores "
"problemas… ¡tendrás que lanzar todo lo que tengas contra ellos!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/10"
msgid "Well done, Soldaten! "
msgstr "¡Bien hecho, Soldados!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/11"
msgid "Good work, keep pushing!"
msgstr "Buen trabajo, ¡sigue empujando!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/12"
msgid "Excellent! Keep up the progress, there is much left to do!"
msgstr "¡Excelente! Sigan avanzando, ¡queda mucho camino por recorrer!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/13"
msgid ""
"The enemy battery has at last ceased to be. An accomplishment that will live "
"long in our future generation's history books, Soldaten!"
msgstr ""
"La batería enemiga por fin ha sido tomada. ¡Un logro que vivirá mucho tiempo "
"en los libros de historia de nuestras futuras generaciones!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/14"
msgid ""
"Excellent work! The control of this route is of upmost importance, this will "
"stop soviets from being able to get in or out of the battery complex."
msgstr ""
"¡Excelente trabajo! El control de esta ruta es de suma importancia, pues "
"impedirá que los soviéticos puedan entrar o salir del búnker de artillería."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/15"
msgid "Good work, the eastern high ground is ours!"
msgstr "Buen trabajo, ¡la colina del este es nuestra!"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/16"
msgid ""
"The minefields have been cleared! Our forces can now safely cross through "
"the northern approaches."
msgstr ""
"¡Los campos de minas han sido despejados! Nuestras fuerzas ahora pueden "
"llegar con seguridad desde el norte."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/narrator/officer/17"
msgid ""
"You are now tasked with clearing the minefields on the north. This will "
"allow our reinforcements to come through."
msgstr ""
"Ahora tienes la tarea de limpiar los campos de minas en el norte. Esto "
"permitirá que nuestros refuerzos puedan llegar sanos y salvos."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/outro_completed"
msgid ""
"Excellent work! The fort has been taken and the entire battery neutralized. "
"The 11th army has its breach in the line and will march on Sevastopol "
"immediately. We will file a favorable report to HQ about your victory at "
"Fort Maksim Gorki! "
msgstr ""
"¡Excelente trabajo! La colina ha sido tomado y toda la batería neutralizada. "
"El 11º ejército ha conseguido una importante brecha en la línea defensiva y "
"marchará sobre Sebastopol inmediatamente. Informaremos favorablemente al "
"cuartel general sobre su victoria en la fortaleza Maksim Gorki"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/outro_failed"
msgid ""
"This is definitely not the kind of outcome we can report to HQ. Our troops "
"were unable to break through, and the attack has come to a complete "
"standstill as a result. You will have to try again after re- grouping, and "
"perhaps using different tactics will help. "
msgstr ""
"Este no es el tipo de resultado del que podemos informar al cuartel general. "
"Nuestras tropas no han podido abrirse paso y el ataque se ha paralizado por "
"completo. Tendrás que volver a intentarlo después de reagrupar, y tal vez "
"convendría usar diferentes tácticas."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/place"
msgid "213th Infantry Regiment, 173rd Engineer Battalion"
msgstr "213º Regimiento de Infantería, 173º Batallón de Ingenieros"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/story"
msgid "The German 11th army is trying to take the last parts of the Crimea that are in Soviet hands. They have taken the Kerch peninsula and now they approach Sevastopol from all sides. The Germans meet stiff resistance from the Black Sea fleet and the 'Separate Coastal Army' under Ivan Yefimovich Petrov. The defenders have dug in everywhere, and they are backed by coastal batteries. Progress is slow, and heavy artillery is brought to the front in an attempt to destroy the defenses and punch through to the city proper.\n\nIn this mission, you will lead the attack on battery number 30, or 'Fort Maksim Gorki 1' as the Germans call it. You will have our heaviest siege mortar at your disposal, use it to silence the defenses. The battery's main guns are already out of action. Use your infantry to protect the left flank. Once you have taken out the first line of defense, storm the hilltop and take the fort. We can't allow any more delays in the offensive. It's up to you to make this work.\n\nGood luck!"
msgstr ""
"El 11º ejército alemán está tratando de tomar las zonas de\n"
"\n"
"Crimea que están en manos soviéticas. Tienen\n"
"\n"
"tomada la península de Kerch y ahora se acercan a Sebastopol\n"
"\n"
"desde todos los lados. Los alemanes encuentran dura resistencia\n"
"\n"
"Por parte de la flota del Mar Negro y el Ejército Costero\n"
"\n"
"bajo el mando de Ivan Yefimovich Petrov\n"
"\n"
"Los defensores se han atrincherado, y están respaldados\n"
"\n"
"por baterías costeras. El progreso es lento, y artillería pesada\n"
"\n"
"es llevada al frente en un intento de destruir\n"
"\n"
"las defensas y penetrar en la ciudad\n"
"\n"
" \n"
"\n"
"En esta misión, dirigirás el ataque a\n"
"\n"
"batería número 30, o ‘Fuerte Maksim Gorki 1’ como\n"
"\n"
"los alemanes lo llaman. Tendrás nuestro más pesado\n"
"\n"
"mortero de asedio a tu disposición, úsalo para silenciar\n"
"\n"
"Las defensas. Los cañones principales de la batería ya están\n"
"\n"
"fuera de servicio. Usa tu infantería para proteger los flancos\n"
"\n"
"Tras lidiar con la primera línea de defensa, asalta la\n"
"\n"
"cima de la colina y toma la fortaleza. No podemos permitir\n"
"\n"
"más retrasos en la ofensiva\n"
"\n"
"Depende de ti que esto funcione\n"
"\n"
" \n"
"\n"
"Buena suerte"

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/task1"
msgid "Clear all of the strongpoints at the first line of defences."
msgstr "Despeja todos los puntos fuertes de la primera línea de defensa."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/task1_1"
msgid "Clear Stongpoint \"Ostrov\"."
msgstr "Despeja el punto fuerte \"Ostrov\"."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/task1_2"
msgid "Clear Strongpoint \"Chicken Farm\"."
msgstr "Despeja el punto fuerte \"Granja de pollos\"."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/task1_3"
msgid "Clear Strongpoint \"Tomato Plant\"."
msgstr "Despeja el punto fuerte \"Planta de Tomate\"."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/task2"
msgid "Clear a way through the minefield."
msgstr "Despeja el campo de minas."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/task3"
msgid "Clear Coastal Battery 30’s Main Battery block."
msgstr "Despeja el bloque de la batería 30."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/task4"
msgid "Clear the Sophia Perovskoy State farm access road."
msgstr "Despejar el camino a la granja Sophia Perovskoy."

msgctxt "mission/single/02-ger/1942_06_sevastopol/task5"
msgid "Clear the Bastion access road."
msgstr "Despeja el camino de acceso al Bastión."
